message.content:
This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:
   - Continue Life Relay implementation from previous session (BRO-267 PTY adapter was complete)
   - Implement BRO-276 (session persistence + reconnect replay buffer)
   - Implement BRO-294 (workspace sidebar with git status)
   - Answer Discord question about xterm.js vs Omnara-style rendering
   - Confirm CI/CD checks pass, merge PR #57, validate via agent browser
   - Fix any issues found during validation

2. Key Technical Concepts:
   - **Life Relay**: Rust daemon (`relayd`) bridging local Claude Code sessions to broomva.tech via HTTP polling
   - **Redis replay buffer**: `RPUSH`/`LTRIM` to capped list (500 events) for SSE reconnect replay
   - **Redis pub/sub**: Per-session output channel for live SSE streaming
   - **DaemonMessage::WorkspaceStatus**: New Rust protocol variant for git polling
   - **Drizzle ORM migrations**: `_journal.json` tracks migration order by idx+tag+when; renumbering idx causes Drizzle to re-run migrations
   - **shadcn Sheet**: Slide-out sidebar component used for workspace sidebar
   - **Omnara-style rendering**: Structured event cards instead of raw xterm.js terminal
   - **camelCase serde**: `#[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]` on each struct variant in Rust protocol

3. Files and Code Sections:

   - **`apps/chat/lib/relay/redis-channels.ts`** — Added replay buffer helpers
     ```typescript
     export function sessionReplayKey(sessionId: string): string {
       return `${PREFIX}:session:${sessionId}:replay`;
     }
     export const REPLAY_BUFFER_SIZE = 500;
     ```

   - **`apps/chat/app/api/relay/events/route.ts`** — Refactored to buffer all session events
     ```typescript
     async function publishSessionEvent(redis, sessionId, payload) {
       const replayKey = sessionReplayKey(sessionId);
       await Promise.all([
         redis.publish(sessionOutputChannel(sessionId), payload),
         redis.rPush(replayKey, payload).then(() =>
           redis.lTrim(replayKey, -REPLAY_BUFFER_SIZE, -1),
         ),
       ]);
     }
     // Cases: output, assistant_message, tool_event, approval_request, workspace_status, session_ended
     ```

   - **`apps/chat/app/api/relay/sessions/[id]/stream/route.ts`** — Drains replay buffer on connect
     ```typescript
     // Short-lived reader for lRange (subscriber can't do regular commands)
     const reader = createClient({ url: process.env.REDIS_URL });
     await reader.connect();
     const buffered = await reader.lRange(replayKey, 0, -1);
     await reader.quit();
     for (const item of buffered) { enqueue(item); }
     controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(": replayed\n\n"));
     await subscriber.subscribe(channel, (message) => { enqueue(message); });
     ```

   - **`relay/crates/life-relay-core/src/protocol.rs`** — Added WorkspaceStatus variant
     ```rust
     /// Workspace git status emitted periodically by relayd.
     #[serde(rename_all = "camelCase")]
     WorkspaceStatus {
         session_id: Uuid,
         branch: Option<String>,
         modified: u32,
         staged: u32,
         last_commit: Option<String>,
     },
     ```

   - **`relay/crates/life-relayd/src/adapters/claude.rs`** — Added git polling + WorkspaceStatus emission
     ```rust
     // Background task: emit git workspace status every 30 s.
     let ws_workdir = config.workdir.clone();
     let ws_tx = event_tx.clone();
     tokio::spawn(async move {
         loop {
             tokio::time::sleep(tokio::time::Duration::from_secs(30)).await;
             let status = git_workspace_status(id, &ws_workdir).await;
             let _ = ws_tx.send(status).await;
         }
     });
     ```
     `git_workspace_status(session_id, workdir)` runs `git rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD`, `git status --porcelain`, `git log -1 --format=%h %s` — all best-effort.

   - **`apps/chat/app/(console)/console/relay/session/[id]/relay-workspace-sidebar.tsx`** — New component
     - shadcn Sheet slide-out from session header
     - Git status section (branch, modified/staged counts, last commit)
     - Node selector dropdown + New Session button
     - Sessions list with status dots linking to `/console/relay/session/[id]`
     - Quick links (Relay Dashboard, Console)

   - **`apps/chat/app/(console)/console/relay/session/[id]/page.tsx`** — Wired sidebar + workspace_status
     ```tsx
     // workspace_status updates sidebar state only — not shown in event feed
     if (event.type === "workspace_status") {
       setWorkspaceStatus(event as WorkspaceStatusMsg);
       return;
     }
     // On reconnect: clear events so replay repopulates cleanly
     es.onopen = () => {
       setConnected(true);
       setEvents([]);
       keyRef.current = 0;
     };
     ```

   - **`apps/chat/components/console-sidebar.tsx`** — Added Relay nav item
     ```tsx
     {
       title: "Relay",
       url: "/console/relay",
       icon: Radio,
       items: [{ title: "Sessions", url: "/console/relay" }],
     },
     ```
     Added `Radio` import from lucide-react.

   - **`apps/chat/lib/db/migrations/meta/_journal.json`** — Attempted fix (caused new issue)
     ```json
     { "idx": 56, "version": "7", "when": 1774540000000, "tag": "0055_add_sandbox_tables", "breakpoints": true },
     { "idx": 57, "version": "7", "when": 1774633286543, "tag": "0056_equal_maginty", "breakpoints": true }
     ```
     Problem: renumbering `0056_equal_maginty` from idx 56 → 57 caused Drizzle to re-run it, but `CREATE TABLE "Agent"` already exists → deployment fails.

   - **`apps/chat/lib/db/migrations/0055_add_sandbox_tables.sql`** — Uses `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` (safe)
   - **`apps/chat/lib/db/migrations/0056_equal_maginty.sql`** — Creates `CREATE TABLE "Agent"` WITHOUT `IF NOT EXISTS` (not idempotent, causes failure)

4. Errors and Fixes:

   - **BRO-275 xterm.js question (Discord)**: User asked if we need xterm.js. Answer: No — `--output-format stream-json` gives typed events rendering as clean structured cards. BRO-275 cancelled.

   - **Journal missing entry for 0055_add_sandbox_tables**: Browser validation found `/console/relay` was 404 and build failing. Fixed by inserting `0055_add_sandbox_tables` at idx 56, renumbering `0056_equal_maginty` to idx 57. But this caused a new failure.

   - **`relation "Agent" already exists` on deployment `5586662`**: `0056_equal_maginty.sql` creates `Agent` table without `IF NOT EXISTS`. When renumbered to idx 57, Drizzle treated it as a new unapplied migration and tried to run it, but `Agent` already exists. Both `b5a820f` AND `5586662` deployments failed — meaning the migration was never cleanly applied. Root cause still being investigated at time of summary.

   - **Relay nav missing from sidebar**: Fixed by adding `Radio` icon + `/console/relay` to `console-sidebar.tsx`.

5. Problem Solving:
   - **xterm.js**: Closed BRO-275 — structured card rendering via stream-json is better UX
